==English==
===Etymology===
French ''[[virer]]''

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪə(r)|-ɪə(r)]]

===Noun===
'''veer'''
#[[turning]].
====Translations====
'''turning'''
*Bosnian: [[skretanje#Bosnian|skretanje]]

===Verb===
'''veer''' ''[[intransitive]]''
#To [[change]] [[direction]] or [[course]] suddenly; to [[swerve]]
#(of the [[wind]]) For the wind to change direction in a [[clockwise]] direction in the [[Northern Hemisphere]] and a [[counterclockwise]] direction in the [[Southern Hemisphere]]. Change in the opposite direction is called '[[back]]'. (from 2002 edition of [[Bowditch]])
#(''nautical'') Of the wind, to shift [[aft]]. Opposite motion is to '[[haul]]' forward. (from 2002 edition of [[Bowditch]])

'''veer''' [[transitive]]
#To turn something

